About the Role 

Sportsbet is seeking a Senior Value Analyst to join our dynamic Customer Generosity team. This role is pivotal in driving the design, implementation, and evaluation of our industry-leading Customer Generosity Program,  delivering value to both customers and the business. 

About You 

You’re a detail-oriented problem solver with a strong eye for patterns and anomalies. You thrive in fast-paced, highly regulated environments and are motivated by protecting customers and ensuring their transactions are seamless and secure. Whether it’s monitoring payments, investigating suspicious activity, or collaborating with stakeholders across the business, you’re proactive, adaptable, and driven to deliver results. 

You bring a customer-first mindset and enjoy working as part of a collaborative team. You’re comfortable using data to guide decisions, confident in juggling multiple priorities, and always looking for ways to improve processes. Above all, you take pride in safeguarding the integrity of our operations while having a bit of fun along the way. 

Key Requirements  

Lead data-driven analysis to guide strategy and investment decisions. 

Design and manage end-to-end experiments and campaigns. 

Provide insightful reporting, segmentation analysis, and performance evaluation. 

Collaborate with cross-functional teams including Data Science, Product, and Marketing. 

Mentor junior analysts and support upskilling in data tools and storytelling.

A NSW government agency is seeking an experienced Principal Business and Financial Analyst to lead high-impact financial modelling and cost-benefit analysis across complex investment programs. This is a long-term contract role running through to March 2026.
You’ll lead the development of business cases aligned with Treasury frameworks, manage financial modelling for strategic initiatives, and provide evidence-based advice to inform public investment decisions. The work is analytical and stakeholder-facing — you'll engage across policy, project, and finance teams to deliver insights that shape funding outcomes.
What you'll do:

Build and maintain advanced financial models using Excel
Conduct cost-benefit analyses and calculate benefit-cost ratios
Provide strategic financial advice on high-value programs
Lead a small team of analysts and guide capability uplift
Engage with internal and external stakeholders, including Treasury
Ensure consistency with NSW Government investment standards
What you’ll bring:

Tertiary qualifications in finance or accounting
Full CA or CPA accreditation
Strong background in financial modelling and scenario planning
Experience in public sector investment frameworks or large organisations
High-level written communication and stakeholder management skills
Political neutrality and ability to obtain a clear police check
This is a strategic contract position suited to a commercially minded public sector finance leader.
To discuss this opportunity confidentially, contact Sarah Purdue sarah.purdue@bluefinresources.com.au

ACCIONA is a global company, leading in the development of regenerative infrastructure that creates a positive impact on society. Our workforce consists of more than 41,500 professionals, present in more than 40 countries across the five continents, all contributing in our mission to design a better planet. Are you a passionate individual who wants to make a difference, promote sustainable development, and find solutions to the biggest global challenges, including climate change, overpopulation, and water scarcity? Come and join us in building the infrastructure our planet needs to achieve a sustainable future.

The Opportunity

This newly created senior role leads the ICT function's performance and continuous improvement initiatives across the ANZ region. It is responsible for driving excellence in service quality, compliance reviews, process optimisation, internal audit, and change management. Acting as a tactical advisor to all IT managers, the role supports the Group Head of ICT in embedding a culture of operational excellence.

It plays a key role in shaping and executing improvement initiatives that enhance ICT service delivery and governance across Australia and New Zealand.

Key responsibilities:


Act as the change management lead for ICT, assessing the impact of change initiatives, identifying key stakeholders, and developing high-level change plans in collaboration with internal communications and designated change agents to ensure smooth transitions and user adoption.
Establish and maintain robust compliance processes and performance indicators, using data insights to identify shortfalls, risks, and opportunities for improvement. Provide timely, actionable intelligence to support governance and strategic planning.
Lead the reporting and analytics practice across the ICT function, supporting IT teams in identifying meaningful KPIs, tracking performance trends, and developing intuitive dashboards and reports that enable data-driven decision-making and transparency across the ANZ region.
Champion process improvement initiatives across the ICT function, applying agile methodologies to streamline workflows, enhance service delivery, and drive operational efficiency. Maintain high-quality process documentation to support consistency and scalability.
Lead a risk-based internal audit function, defining the scope, timing, and depth of audit activities. Coordinate effectively with external vendors and internal stakeholders to ensure structured documentation, clear reporting, and follow-through on recommended actions.

About You:

Strong background in compliance, audit, and process improvement, ideally with Big 4 or professional services experience.
An internal control specialist exhibiting exemplary skills in evaluation internal controls in business processes.
Proven success in leading change initiatives and engaging diverse stakeholders.
Excellent communicator with strong influencing skills.
Bachelor's degree in IT, Business, or related field; certifications in ITIL, Agile, Change Management, or Internal Audit preferred.

About Chamonix:

Welcome to Chamonix IT Solutions, where innovation meets passion. We're an end-to-end technical services provider committed to helping businesses excel in the digital era. Established in 2010 and recently acquired by Synechron, a global consulting firm delivering industry-leading digital solutions, we’re poised for significant growth! Our local, dedicated team of 150 professionals specialises in guiding our clients through transformative journeys - from groundbreaking digital transformations to comprehensive technical delivery and ongoing managed support.

Our dynamic team is the cornerstone of our success, driven by a culture of collaboration, continuous learning, and a relentless pursuit of excellence. At Chamonix, we are not merely keeping pace with the market; we are leading it, delivering exceptional outcomes that empower our clients to stay ahead of the curve. Join us and be part of a journey where the future is shaped daily.

The role:

We’re looking for a Senior Business Analyst to join our Adelaide team, working on a major infrastructure project within the defence sector. While your initial focus will be on a high-profile program, your broad skill set across both applications and infrastructure will ensure you’re well-placed to make an impact on a variety of future client engagements. From discovery to delivery, you’ll be part of high-impact initiatives that keep you engaged and growing!

What you’ll be doing:

• Partnering with stakeholders to gather, analyse, and document business and technical requirements for large-scale projects.

• Translating complex technical and business needs into clear, actionable deliverables.

• Working across infrastructure and application domains - from data and systems integration to operational process improvements.

• Leading workshops, interviews, and requirements sessions with a wide range of stakeholders.

• Collaborating closely with project managers, architects, engineers, and vendors to ensure smooth delivery.

What you’ll bring:

• Extensive experience as a Senior Business Analyst in complex technical environments.

• Proven ability to work across applications, infrastructure, and integration projects.

• Strong analytical skills, with the ability to quickly understand and translate business needs.

• Excellent communication and facilitation skills, with experience in managing diverse stakeholder groups.

• Background in the defence sector or other highly regulated industries (preferred).

• Consulting experience preferred but not essential

• MUST have Australian Citizenship and ability to obtain (or currently hold) a Defence security clearance.

What makes us a great place to work?

At Chamonix, we value our culture and believe it is essential to our continued success. We bring together top best technical experts, driving innovation and collaboration at every level. We are proud to foster a supportive, driven, flexible, and inclusive environment that empowers our people to grow, learn, and achieve their personal and professional goals. Recognised as a Great Place to Work 2025/26, and as the #17 Best Workplace™ in Technology by Great Place To Work Australia 2025! We are dedicated to investing in our employees and offer a range of holistic perks and benefits to support individual needs, including:

• Competitive salary package

• Hybrid working model and flexible hours (client dependent)

• Centrally located offices in Adelaide CBD

• Extensive professional development opportunities, including annual professional training allowance, Lunch and Learns, paid training and exam leave

• Annual technology allowance

• Mentoring and career progression opportunities

• Discounted health insurance, anniversary gifts, corporate discounts on various products and services

• Employee Recognition Program and Quarterly/Annual Awards celebrating outstanding contributions

• Employee Assistance Program

• An active social club, Friday drinks and various social events scattered throughout the year

https://www.synechron.com/en-au

www.chamonix.com.au

Next steps…

We appreciate the time you have taken to apply for a role with us. Chamonix is an equal opportunity employer and welcomes applications from individuals of all backgrounds. Our hiring decisions are based on your experience, skills, enthusiasm, and your future potential in the role. If you feel that you meet some, but not all the requirements above, we still encourage you to apply. If you are invited to an interview, please advise us if you require any reasonable adjustments during the interview process, and what pronouns you use.

Chamonix is committed to creating an inclusive and respectful workplace for all employees. Differences are embraced, contributions are valued, and everyone has a sense of connection and belonging. We welcome people with diverse skills, experiences, perspectives and backgrounds and encourage applications from Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander peoples, and individuals who may identify as LGBTIQ, with disability, a culturally diverse background, and people of all ages.

Please note that we receive a large number of applications and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted

About the opportunity:

We are currently seeking an experienced Senior Change Analyst accountable for facilitating and driving change and end user adoption of new programs, systems and processes across the organisation through communication, training and business engagement

The role will be fully immersed from the outset of projects commencing, working across a wide range of stakeholders, and focussing on ensuring the successful execution of programs and projects and other key strategic initiatives.

The Senior Change Analyst is accountable for:

Conducting change analysis, proposing change approaches and delivering change in line with the organisation’s change management strategy and methodology
Producing change artefacts, training and communication materials and project documentation for change initiatives
Contributing to the enablement of key stakeholders across the organisation, facilitating familiarity with change concepts and practices
Liaising with project and system leaders and collaborating with change and project teams to deliver best-fit situational and general change approaches to facilitate the effective and timely delivery of projects and initiatives
Building a detailed understanding of the diverse staff groups within the organisation, ensuring open communication with organisational-wide specialists and leaders
Utilising measurement systems to track adoption, utilisation and proficiency of change projects and initiatives, ensuring transparency and reportability

About you:

To be successful in this highly rewarding role, you will:

Be supportive of the ethos of the Catholic Church
Participate in staff liturgical and formation opportunities
Understand and contribute to the delivery and continuous improvement of relevant strategic initiatives and operational plans
Engage in continuous learning and contribute positively to a collaborative and respectful working environment aligned with the culture and values of CSPD

In return:

Competitive remuneration
Salary packaging
Parental leave
Flexible work arrangements include a hybrid working model
Wellbeing programs
Professional development opportunities 

Interested?

This position involves working with children. The appointment of successful applicants will be subject to satisfactory employment screening for child-related employment including the completion of a National Police Check, retention of a valid Working with Children Check and adoption and compliance with CSPD’s Child Safeguarding Procedures and Code of Conduct When Working with Students and Children. About us:

At CSPD we are committed to responding to the needs of students in a world that is changing rapidly. With over 5,000 passionate employees located across our primary and secondary schools, we have the intent and the resources to transform the learning and unlock the full potential of each of our 40,000 plus students. We are always on the lookout for top talent to help us achieve our strategic goal of inspiring the future, through quality catholic schooling and by strengthening the professional lives of our employees.

Apply today!

At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues. We know work and life are intertwined. That's why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members.

Your New Role

As the Senior Manager, Member Research, you will play a pivotal role in driving Member & Market insights and research across the Member Domain. Reporting to the Principal, Member Strategy & Insights, you will lead a small team responsible for understanding member preferences and behaviours, tracking market trends, and embedding research into all activity.

You'll work closely with colleagues and external partners to ensure member needs are understood and addressed, using robust market research programs and segmentation strategies. Your leadership will foster a high-performing, diverse, and engaged team, driving innovation and continuous improvement. This is a senior role with the opportunity to make a significant impact on member outcomes and the Fund's strategic ambitions, and it would ideally suit someone with a background in an organisation with a large customer / membership base, or with strong agency experience.

What You'll Need

Significant and in-depth, professional experience in market research or related fields, straddling brand, innovation, creative and CX, including experience managing a Research Team
Proven track record in designing and executing robust market research quantitative and qualitative programs, ideally in service industries (e.g., telco, utilities, financial services)
Experience in utilising tools such as Q and Qualtrics (or similar),
A desire and ability to manage and execute projects yourself
Deep working knowledge of member/customer segmentations.
An innovative thinker, with experience of program optimisation and an ability to demonstrate ROI of research programs
A Team Player that can establish and evolve relationships internally and with external partners
Someone that has OR is wanting to promote the great work beyond AustralianSuper walls, inspiring fellow research practitioners
Demonstrated ability to lead diverse and dispersed teams to achieve objectives.
Advanced written and oral communication skills, with the ability to present ideas and insights to senior management and large audiences.
Advanced analytical and organisational skills, with a high attention to detail.
Experience managing team budgets, workforce planning, and cost-efficiency.
Ability to work with and incorporate multiple data sources.
Experience working under pressure, managing multiple priorities, and meeting deadlines.
Tertiary qualifications in a business or related field (e.g., Bachelor of Business, Management, Commerce, Finance, Accounting, Marketing, or Economics).

Life at AustralianSuper

AustralianSuper is committed to colleague development, and we support our people with ongoing learning, coaching and training, as well as career opportunities across our expanding global organisation. We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we're happy to discuss what this looks like for you.

We cultivate a workplace that champions safety, respect, inclusiveness and diversity. We are committed to supporting our diverse workforce in a way that is inclusive and embraces diversity in all its forms. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process or the role, please let our recruitment team know.

What's Next

Apply now, if you share our values of Energy, Integrity, Generosity of Spirit and Excellent Outcomes and would like the opportunity to work in a challenging, growing and rapidly evolving team to deliver outstanding results.

Australian or New Zealand citizenship or Australian permanent residency status is required.

Progress powered by purpose.

Who We Are
Xenco provides businesses with executive and operational level support, significantly enhancing productivity, efficiencies, and company profitability. Our expertise lies in rapidly understanding business issues, formulating achievable plans, and executing them to deliver measurable improvements to our client's bottom line.

The Opportunity
We are seeking a Financial Analyst, to join our mining client. This is a role with a duration of 2-3 months renewable. It will be a mix of site based and work from home.  

What the Role Entails:

Budget Development
Budgeting and Forecasting: Support preparation of annual budgets and periodic forecasts, working collaboratively with department heads to ensure accuracy and alignment with strategic goals
Identify opportunities for process improvement and optimisation within financial processes and systems
Stakeholder Engagement: Build strong relationships with stakeholders across the organisation, fostering collaboration and communication to achieve shared financial objectives
Manage Reporting & Financial Analysis 
What You Will Need:

Relevant Qualification
Previous experience in the Heavy Industry
proficiency in financial modelling and data analysis tools
Why Join Us:
We seek ambitious individuals who can use their initiative to drive outcomes. This role offers competitive rates and provides rapid and diverse experiences. Work with industry experts and gain exposure to a broad range of interesting projects.
If you are interested in this opportunity, please apply below. We will contact you soon.
We thank all applicants for their interest.

Job Summary

6 Month Contract, strong views of permanency
Located close to Mascot with 2-3 days work from home
Exciting Opportunity to Work within a Global Organisation 


The Organisation
Our client is a leader in sustainable operations and data-driven logistics solutions. They are looking for a Senior Operational Analyst to join their team. The successful applicant will be integral in using advanced analytics to drive optimisation across loading operations, enhancing efficiency, cost-effectiveness, and sustainability.


This is a 6-month contract with potential for strong views of extension to 12 months. The business values professional growth and offers substantial training and development to ensure you succeed in this high-impact role.


The Opportunity
As a Senior Operational Analyst in their optimisation team, you will be responsible for identifying and quantifying optimisation opportunities using advanced analytics. You will design analytical frameworks, build predictive models, and collaborate with cross-functional teams to drive strategic recommendations that deliver tangible improvements in operational efficiency and sustainability.


Your responsibilities will include:

Designing analytical frameworks to solve complex loading optimisation challenges.
Building and maintaining predictive models for load efficiency and customer consumption patterns.
Analysing waste trends and consumption data to identify root causes and opportunities for improvement.
Collaborating with operations and supply chain teams to implement data-driven optimisation strategies.
Developing scenario models to evaluate different loading approaches and their impact on costs, efficiency, and emissions.
Providing actionable insights and recommendations to improve efficiency and reduce waste.
 

Skills and Experience

Experience with statistical modelling, forecasting, or optimisation techniques.
Ability to communicate complex insights clearly and engage effectively with diverse stakeholders across operations, leadership, and cross-functional teams.
Experience in shaping analysis frameworks and influencing decision-making.
A strategic mindset with the ability to identify patterns and simplify complexity.
3-5+ years of experience in solving complex operational challenges through advanced analytics.
Experience designing and implementing data-driven solutions in fast-paced business environments.

Why join the project?

Make a real impact, drive smarter operations and shape future practices, all while delivering strong enviornmental and business results. 

Hours of Work
Available to work Monday - Friday. For more information, you can contact Mia at email mia.kovacevich@teksystems.com quoting Job Reference 544590. Alternatively, apply here to register your interest.

About the Company
Davidson is proud to be partnering with a leading Australian university on the search for a skilled Reporting Business Analyst. This contract role will play a pivotal part in ensuring the university meets its compliance obligations while delivering accurate insights to guide strategic decisions.

About the Role
As a Reporting Business Analyst, you will provide hands-on expertise across regulatory reporting and business process improvement within Higher Education systems, particularly TCSI (Transforming the Collection of Student Information). Your work will directly support the university's ability to meet statutory obligations, enhance data integrity, and streamline reporting practices.

Key Responsibilities

Manage, validate, and submit TCSI and other statutory reporting requirements accurately and on time.
Analyse complex student, course, and enrolment data to identify issues, trends, and opportunities for improvement.
Partner with stakeholders, IT teams, and government agencies to resolve reporting queries and data quality issues.
Translate business requirements into clear, actionable specifications for reporting and system enhancements.
Develop documentation, data dictionaries, and process maps to support compliance and transparency.
Contribute to continuous improvement initiatives across student information and reporting systems.

About You

Solid experience in university reporting and TCSI compliance.
Strong data analysis and problem-solving skills.
Ability to translate complex requirements into clear outcomes.
Skilled at collaborating with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.

The Benefits

Initial 6-12 month contract with extensions highly likely.
Opportunity to work on a high-impact role in the Higher Education sector.
Supportive and collaborative environment.
South East Location - 2 -3 days per week in office


Please apply with current resume in Microsoft Word format only (.doc or .docx). If you have the relevent experience listed above and require further information, please contact Tara Gearon at tara.gearon@davidsonwp.com quoting reference JN -092025-41392. Want to know more about Davidson? Visit us at www.davidsonwp.com

Head of Data and Technology

Lead our data transformation.

Drive impact for our Club and community.

Full-time permanent employment with WA Business’s Employer of the Year 2024.

 This role will elevate how Fremantle Football Club uses data to drive decisions and create value. Building on our strong foundation in IT services, insights and analytics, you will bring deep data engineering expertise to accelerate our shift to a truly data-driven organisation. The role combines strategic leadership with hands-on delivery to deliver future-ready solutions.

About the Role

Reporting to the Executive General Manager of People, Strategy & Community, you will lead our Data and Technology Function, with direct reports in IT, data engineering and digital enablement. Your focus will be enabling evidence-based decision-making and driving innovation through data, automation and AI.

The scope of the role will include:

Defining and delivering the Club’s data and technology strategy.

Building and optimising data pipelines, integrations and governance frameworks.

Leading digital innovation, including automation and AI/ML adoption.

Partnering with business units to embed data-driven decision-making.

Elevating data quality, security, and compliance standards.

What your will bring

We are seeking a candidate who brings:

A degree in IT, Data Science, Computer Science or related field or demonstrated equivalent experience.

Strong background in data engineering, governance and enterprise data strategy.

Experience building scalable data platforms and pipelines in cloud environments.

Ability to balance team leadership with hands-on technical delivery.

Current or willingness to obtain a National Police Clearance and Working with Children Check.

What we offer

Joining Fremantle Football Club means more than a job, it means being part of a values-led team with strong community impact. You’ll enjoy:

Competitive salary package.

Flexible and hybrid working options.

Season passes and free parking.

All of Club Bonus Scheme.

Six months paid parental leave after 12 months of service.

Service recognition awards and partner discounts.

A culture that values growth, belonging and excellence.

Who we are

The Fremantle Football Club, also known as the "Freo Dockers," competes in both the AFL and AFLW. Honoured as WA Business Awards Employer of the Year 2024, we are proud to be a purpose-driven organisation. Guided by our Anchors – Club First, Authentic, Heart, Connection and Best Self – we are committed to enriching our community and making the Freo family proud.

What’s next

Applications are open for one month from this advertisement. Shortlisting will begin in two weeks. To apply, please submit your application online. Candidates of initial interest will be contacted for further discussions. If you have support or access requirements, please let us know at the time of application.

Our Commitment

We celebrate diversity and foster an inclusive workplace where everyone has the opportunity to thrive. We welcome applications from people of all backgrounds, experiences and identities.

Unsolicited applications from recruitment agencies will not be accepted.

About the Role

As the Data and Analytics Manager at QLeave, you will lead a small, dedicated team to deliver meaningful insights and drive data-led decision-making across our organisation. Your work will directly contribute to improving service delivery and ensuring the long-term sustainability of Queensland's portable long service leave schemes.

Reporting to the Director, Technology, Data and Building Services, you will provide strategic leadership for QLeave's analytics function, champion data governance, oversee contemporary analytics platforms, and enable key decision-making through robust data analysis, modelling, and visualisation.

You'll also play a key role on QLeave's leadership team, helping to shape the organisation's future through evidence-based insight and continuous improvement.

Key Responsibilities

Lead and mentor the Data and Analytics team, developing capability and fostering a culture of high performance, innovation and continuous learning.
Oversee the development and maintenance of QLeave's analytics and business intelligence (BI) environment, ensuring governance, accessibility and reliability.
Drive organisation-wide use of data to improve planning, performance evaluation and service outcomes.
Engage with internal and external stakeholders to understand data needs and deliver tailored, fit-for-purpose insights and visualisations.
Prepare expert advice, models, and reports to inform operational improvements and strategic investments.
Promote data integrity, metadata management and system integration in line with best practice.
Proactively identify development opportunities for your team and manage performance expectations to support organisational goals.

For more details, please refer to the full role description.

What We're Looking For

QLeave appointments are based on selecting the eligible applicant best suited to the position.  We will assess your application based on your experience, potential for development, and your personal qualities.

We are seeking an experienced, future-focused leader who brings strong technical capability and an ability to lead through influence.

You will ideally demonstrate:

Proven experience in data analytics, business intelligence, modelling and strategic reporting.
Assist in the development and implementation of a data strategy and roadmap.
Excellent leadership and mentoring skills with the ability to build team capability and manage performance.
Critical strategic approach to delivering data solutions.
Advanced skills in data visualisation and analysis using tools like Power BI, SQL, and cloud-based platforms.
Knowledge of data governance, system integration, and metadata management.
Exceptional stakeholder engagement and the ability to translate data into meaningful insights that influence decision-makers.
Strategic thinking and sound judgment in applying data to support corporate priorities.

There are no mandatory qualifications for this role. However, relevant experience or certifications in analytics, data science, IT or public sector management will be well regarded.

Conditions and Benefits

Convenient Northgate location with free on-site parking.
Competitive salary with up to 12.75% superannuation contributions.
Generous leave entitlements, including 17.5% annual leave loading.
Flexible work arrangements and supportive hybrid environment
Opportunities for professional development and career growth.

How to Apply

If you're ready to apply your technical expertise in a purpose-driven organisation and help shape the future of data at QLeave, we encourage you to apply.

Your application must include:

A detailed resume outlining your qualifications and experience.
A capability statement (1-2 pages) demonstrating how your skills align with the role's requirements.

For further information or a confidential discussion, please contact Robert O'Brien.  

QLeave values diversity and is committed to being an equal opportunity employer. Adjustments to the recruitment process are available upon request to ensure all candidates can showcase their abilities.

At ASIC, you can be the change that ensures a fair, strong and efficient financial system for the benefit of all Australians. Contribute to delivering on ASIC's purpose, vision, and strategic priorities to help maintain the integrity of the financial system and protect consumers from harm.

 

Implement best practice surveillance and supervision to achieve robust and impactful regulatory outcomes. Seeking an expert in complex, risk-based surveillance and supervision with exceptional stakeholder relationship skills.

 

All locations considered
Permanent position
Salary from $152,074 + 15.4% superannuation
Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, 9 October 2025.

 

The team

The Strategic Surveillance, Banking and Data (SSBD) team delivers proactive surveillance outcomes across multiple sectors using thematic surveillance expertise, running complex surveillances within and across sectors and leading group wide activities.

SSBD is responsible for the regulation and supervision of the banking sector and strategically important financial institutions. This includes proactive engagement with and monitoring of firms to understand and respond to emerging industry issues and provide strategic direction and technical expertise for ASIC's work.

The team collaborates with other parts of ASIC in ensuring consistent and effective delivery of ASIC's regulatory priorities by using best practice regulatory supervision, surveillance knowledge, expertise, and resources on Regulation & Supervision (R&S) or ASIC wide projects.

 

The role

As a Senior Analyst/Lawyer/Supervisor you will be responsible for:

Making significant contributions to the delivery of complex data driven surveillances and ASIC wide or priority projects.
Making significant and strategic contributions to the supervision of the banking sector including identification of and addressing emerging and current risks, stakeholder engagement and assessing applications to exercise discretionary powers.
Developing and maintaining key internal and external relationships with stakeholders, including representing ASIC at government or industry meetings 
Leading and identifying new ways to utilise data to deliver priorities and support evidence based decision making, including effective collection, management, analysis, and communication of insights from data.
Contributing to the guidance, training, direction and mentoring of junior team members.
Maintaining knowledge of ASIC's regulatory framework and toolkit, relevant legislative and reporting requirements, domestic and international developments, and best industry practice models.

 

About you

You will possess a strong understanding of the benefits of strategic relationships to maximise data and information opportunities, with experience in advising on complex transactions or projects requiring critical thinking and judgment in relevant industries such as legal firms, or regulatory environments.

You will also demonstrate:

Relevant tertiary qualification.
Deep knowledge of banking, Australian financial markets, and regulatory environment.
Strong strategic thinking, analytical, investigative, and research skills.
Proven ability to develop strategic relationships for effective data use.
Experience leading high-performing teams with a focus on strategic direction and coaching.
Excellent communication skills and attention to detail in business reporting.

 

About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms.

 

ASIC is committed to a providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Indigenous Australians are encouraged to apply as well as applicants from all backgrounds and with different abilities.

 

We offer a range of employee benefits including:

Attractive superannuation
Additional leave entitlements
50/50 hybrid work-from home model
Flexible work arrangements
Assistance for study and professional development

Click here to view ASIC's salary and benefits guide.

To read more about ASIC, you can visit our website or review our Corporate Plan.

To work with us, you need to be an Australian citizen and be prepared to complete an ASIC Suitability and Baseline Assessment.

Product Owner – Wealth Investment | Regulatory Focus

Up to $180k base + super
Sydney CBD – 3 days per week onsite
Exciting new projects | Portfolio of Wealth Investment Products

We’re recruiting for a Product Owner with strong Business Analyst experience to join a leading organisation in the wealth and investment space. This is an exciting opportunity to work across a product portfolio, driving delivery of new initiatives while ensuring compliance with upcoming regulatory changes and upgrades.

You’ll play a key role in shaping product strategy, partnering with stakeholders, and ensuring the delivery team has clear direction and a well-prioritised roadmap. With plenty of new projects coming up, this role offers a chance to make a real impact in a dynamic and fast-paced environment.
What you’ll be doing
Owning the product vision, roadmap and backlog across a wealth investment product portfolio.
Leading initiatives focused on regulatory changes and system upgrades.
Working closely with Business Analysts, developers, and stakeholders to deliver customer-focused solutions.
Ensuring requirements are clearly defined, user stories are prioritised, and delivery teams are set up for success.
Tracking progress and communicating updates to key stakeholders.
Driving efficiencies and improvements to enhance both client and internal user experiences.
What we’re looking for
Previous experience as a Product Owner with a background in Business Analysis.
Strong understanding of wealth management, investment products, and regulatory frameworks. 
Proven ability to translate complex business needs into effective solutions.
Exceptional communication and stakeholder management skills.
Pragmatic, detail-oriented, and able to thrive in a fast-moving environment.
Formal Product Owner certification (CSPO, PSPO) highly regarded.
Why you’ll love this role
Competitive salary package – up to $180k base + super.
Hybrid working – 3 days per week in Sydney CBD.
Exposure to new and exciting projects in a high-profile wealth investment environment.
Collaborative and supportive delivery team culture.
If you’re a driven Product Owner who enjoys bridging the gap between business and technology, and you’re keen to take ownership of products that sit at the heart of wealth investment services, we’d love to hear from you.

The team

The Strategic Surveillance, Banking and Data (SSBD) team delivers proactive surveillance outcomes across multiple sectors using thematic surveillance expertise, running complex surveillances within and across sectors and leading group wide activities.

SSBD is responsible for the regulation and supervision of the banking sector and strategically important financial institutions. This includes proactive engagement with and monitoring of firms to understand and respond to emerging industry issues and provide strategic direction and technical expertise for ASIC's work.

The team collaborates with other parts of ASIC in ensuring consistent and effective delivery of ASIC's regulatory priorities by using best practice regulatory supervision, surveillance knowledge, expertise, and resources on Regulation & Supervision (R&S) or ASIC wide projects.

 

The role

As a Senior Analyst/Lawyer/Supervisor you will be responsible for:

Making significant contributions to the delivery of complex data driven surveillances and ASIC wide or priority projects.
Making significant and strategic contributions to the supervision of the banking sector including identification of and addressing emerging and current risks, stakeholder engagement and assessing applications to exercise discretionary powers.
Developing and maintaining key internal and external relationships with stakeholders, including representing ASIC at government or industry meetings 
Leading and identifying new ways to utilise data to deliver priorities and support evidence based decision making, including effective collection, management, analysis, and communication of insights from data.
Contributing to the guidance, training, direction and mentoring of junior team members.
Maintaining knowledge of ASIC's regulatory framework and toolkit, relevant legislative and reporting requirements, domestic and international developments, and best industry practice models.

 

About you

You will possess a strong understanding of the benefits of strategic relationships to maximise data and information opportunities, with experience in advising on complex transactions or projects requiring critical thinking and judgment in relevant industries such as legal firms, or regulatory environments.

You will also demonstrate:

Relevant tertiary qualification.
Deep knowledge of banking, Australian financial markets, and regulatory environment.
Strong strategic thinking, analytical, investigative, and research skills.
Proven ability to develop strategic relationships for effective data use.
Experience leading high-performing teams with a focus on strategic direction and coaching.
Excellent communication skills and attention to detail in business reporting.

 

About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms.

 

ASIC is committed to a providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Indigenous Australians are encouraged to apply as well as applicants from all backgrounds and with different abilities.

 

We offer a range of employee benefits including:

Attractive superannuation
Additional leave entitlements
50/50 hybrid work-from home model
Flexible work arrangements
Assistance for study and professional development
